race.description: Woodford Racing Club Life Members Maiden Plate
race.comment: RUSSIAN ROYALTY (14) peaks and is ready to win off solid efforts at Kilmore and Stawell last time when she was stepping up to this trip. The filly sits at the bottom of the handicap and maps for a soft run. COWARRIE (1) finished a touch ahead of the above in the same contest, coming back in trip. He's switched yards and had been freshened. Looks back on track and the odds will be a lot shorter in this. TUPAC (8) wasn't beaten too far in the same contest as the favourite and will be fitter. Has a key gear switch, but is going to need some luck from a wide gate. SEA DANGER (6) peaks off a narrow defeat at Horsham over 1800m. Has scope for further improvement and can feature with a good ride. FOX STRIKE (2) comes out of the same race and fitter should be around the mark.
